printf -- print formatted text to output

"" -- indicates strings

printf("String"); //prints string "String" but does print newline.
printf("String\n"); // prints string "String" and newline. '\n' is an escape sequence. Special character.

'\t' is tab special character 

printf("%s is the best person ever!\n", "David");
After comma, other arguments are variables to be substitued with placeholders in order

printf("I am %d years old\n", 24);
printf("pi is %f\n", 3.141592635) ; //3.141593
printf("pi is %.2f\n, 3.141592635); //3.14

% - signifies placehold for printf
	%s 	-- string
	%d 	-- decimal integer
	%f 	-- floating point number. 6 decimal places by default
	%.2 	-- specify decimal places for floating point
